open62541's housekeeping sends the keepalive ReadRequest driven by connectivityCheckInterval
(which Qt's plugin enables) as soon as lastConnectivityCheck -- initially 0 -- is older than
the interval, without checking that a session exists. During a connect to a remote server the
handshake runs long enough for that tick to fire on the session-less SecureChannel opened for
endpoint validation. Strict UA servers (e.g. Prosys) answer the read with a ServiceFault,
open62541 takes it for the pending GetEndpoints response and aborts the connect with
BadSessionClosed. Local servers complete the handshake before the tick, so only remote
connections fail.

diff --git a/src/3rdparty/open62541/open62541.c b/src/3rdparty/open62541/open62541.c
--- a/src/3rdparty/open62541/open62541.c
+++ b/src/3rdparty/open62541/open62541.c
@@ -60531,6 +60531,9 @@ __Client_backgroundConnectivity(UA_Client *client) {
     if(!client->config.connectivityCheckInterval)
         return;

+    if(client->sessionState != UA_SESSIONSTATE_ACTIVATED)
+        return; /* ouaexp patch: no keepalive read without a session */
+
     if(client->pendingConnectivityCheck)
         return;

